    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Sir F.
                        Bruce</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1867-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 24, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Having submitted to the Secretary of the Navy the
                    communication of the 3d instant addressed to this department by yourself on the
                    subject of the signal code of the navy of the United States, I have the honor to
                    enclose, in reply, a copy of a letter of the 15th instant from the Secretary of
                    the Navy, and of the paper which accompanied it.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. Sir <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick Wright Bruce,</hi> &amp;<hi
                            rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi
                            rend="italic">c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
